JOHANNESBURG - The court challenge against Brian Molefe's reinstatement as Eskom CEO goes ahead on Tuesday.It'll be heard in the North Gauteng High Court.WATCH: Molefe's decision to take Eskom to court appalling: AnalystThe DA, EFF and union Solidarity are leading the legal bid. The decision to reappoint Molefe as Eskom chief executive has since been rescinded, but they argue a court should overturn it, because it was illegal. Meanwhile, Molefe has also challenged his dismissal. He applied to the Labour Court to declare his sacking unlawful.The former Eskom chief executive said he needs to be on the job in order to fight the High Court challenge.eNCA